SERVER creation - NODE AND EXPRESS

BASIC COMMANDS

1 CREATING Package.json - npm init
2 INSTALL Express - npm i Express
3 Install JWT - npm i jsonwebtoken
4 Install mongoose - npm i mongoose 
5 Install cross - npm i cors

BASIC STEPS

1 Creating a folder 
2 Creating package.json file
3 Install Express
4 Create index.js file
5 import express inside index.js file
6 create app using Express 
7 setup port number
8 Resolving http request
9 HTTP Response code
  1xx - Information
  2xx - Success
  3xx - Redirection
  4xx - Client error
  5xx - Server error

10 JWT(JSON Web Tocken) - Authentication

      server generated token          request number
login ------------------------> client----------------->server------->

Token generate - sign()

11 Middleware
  1. Application specific middleware - for entire application 
  2. Router specific miidleware - for token validations - jwtMiddleware
      verify() - token validation

12 Database Integration
    Using mongoose
    Database connection
    create model using mongoose

13 Asynchronous function Resolving
    Resolve - .then()
    Reject - catch()

14 CORS - CROSS ORIGIN RESOURCE SHARING
    Install cors